      "title": "Mutating Bash can land production changes before the review gate runs",
      "evidence": "The PostToolUse backstop explicitly says it is not primary enforcement and cannot undo the already-written file. Because the no-discretion production gate is registered only for Edit/Write/MultiEdit, a Bash write such as a heredoc or redirect can modify a production .go file before any review completion exists; the backstop only creates a pending obligation afterward.",
      "recommendation": "Add a PreToolUse Bash classifier/deny for mutating commands that target gated paths, or restrict mutating Bash broadly while no_discretion is enabled. Keep PostToolUse only as defense-in-depth.",
