      "title": "Review-completion audit checks accept unbound legacy events",
      "evidence": "The production trigger accepts audit events where event is either obligation_completed or granted and only checks exception_id/cycle_id. If binding.prev_audit_sha is empty, chain_ok becomes true without requiring review_type or scope_hash to match. Plan/test have similar weaker fallbacks, so an approved completion can be paired with an unrelated legacy-style audit line.",
      "recommendation": "For review-completion types, require a valid full audit chain plus an obligation_completed event whose exception_id, cycle_id, review_type, and scope_hash exactly match the candidate. Do not accept granted legacy events for v1.9 review completions.",
